A 41-year- old security officer was shot and killed in a hail of bullets in Besters, KwaMashu, west of Durban, on Thursday morning. It is alleged that the security officer was in the process of boarding a mini-bus taxi when he was approached by a man. According to the private security company, Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA), the man was dressed in blue shorts, sandals and a navy sleeveless jacket. The man shot the officer at least ten times. Rusa’s spokesperson, Prem Balram, said the gunman fled without stealing anything. Balram said the officer was dressed in his company uniform and was en route to Phoenix when he was attacked. “Rusa Phoenix Operations Center received numerous calls at approximately 5am from frantic onlookers requesting medical assistance for the victim. Reaction Officers and RUSA Medics were immediately dispatched however on arrival they discovered that the man had succumbed to his injuries...the motive for the shooting remains unknown at this stage,” said Balram.